TITLE: Using Collision Categories in Arcade Physics
DESCRIPTION: Creating and assigning physics collision categories to control which objects can collide with each other. Up to 32 unique categories can be defined per world.
SOURCE: https://github.com/phaserjs/phaser/blob/master/changelog/3.70/CHANGELOG-v3.70.md#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
// Create collision categories
const CATEGORY_PLAYER = this.physics.world.nextCategory();
const CATEGORY_ENEMY = this.physics.world.nextCategory();
const CATEGORY_BULLET = this.physics.world.nextCategory();
const CATEGORY_WALL = this.physics.world.nextCategory();

// Assign categories
player.setCollisionCategory(CATEGORY_PLAYER);
enemies.setCollisionCategory(CATEGORY_ENEMY);
bullets.setCollisionCategory(CATEGORY_BULLET);
walls.setCollisionCategory(CATEGORY_WALL);

// Configure what each category collides with
player.setCollidesWith([CATEGORY_ENEMY, CATEGORY_WALL]);
enemies.setCollidesWith([CATEGORY_PLAYER, CATEGORY_BULLET, CATEGORY_WALL]);
bullets.setCollidesWith([CATEGORY_ENEMY, CATEGORY_WALL]);

// Reset to default collision (collides with everything)
sprite.resetCollision();
```

