TITLE: Loading and Creating Shaders in Phaser 3
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to load a GLSL shader file in preload and create a shader game object. The shader is loaded using the GLSL File Loader and then instantiated as a game object with specific dimensions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/phaserjs/phaser/blob/master/changelog/3.17/CHANGELOG-v3.17.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function preload () {
    this.load.glsl('fire', 'shaders/fire.glsl.js');
}

function create () {
    this.add.shader('fire', 400, 300, 512, 512);
}
```

