TITLE: Implementing Animation Events in Phaser 3
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the new animation events in Phaser 3, replacing the previous callback system. This allows for more specific control over animations for individual game objects.
SOURCE: https://github.com/phaserjs/phaser/blob/master/changelog/3.4/CHANGELOG-v3.4.md#2025-04-16_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
sprite.on('animationstart', function() {
    // Code to run when animation starts
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Testing WebGL Context Loss and Restore in Phaser
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to simulate WebGL context loss and restoration using the WEBGL_lose_context extension. The code forces context loss after 1 second and restores it after another second, useful for testing context restoration handling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/phaserjs/phaser/blob/master/changelog/3.80/WebGLContextRestore.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const webGLLoseContextExtension = game.renderer.getExtension('WEBGL_lose_context');

setTimeout(function () {
    webGLLoseContextExtension.loseContext();
    setTimeout(function () {
        webGLLoseContextExtension.restoreContext();
    }, 1000)
}, 1000);
```

